EXERCISE 1.3

===================================================================================================================================

ðŸ”¹ 3. Copy, Move, Rename

cp file dest				#Copy file
cp -i file dest				#Copy with confirmation
cp -r dir dest				#Copy directory
mv file dest				#Move file
mv old new					#Rename file
mv -i old new				#Prompt before overwrite


===================================================================================================================================

EXERCISE 1.4

===================================================================================================================================

ðŸ”¹ 4. Viewing & Reading File Content

cat file					#Display entire file
tac file					#Display file in reverse
nl file						#Show numbered lines
less file					#Scroll file (best for logs)
more file					#View file page by page
head file					#Show first 10 lines
head -n 20 file				#Show first 20 lines
tail file					#Show last 10 lines
tail -n 50 file				#Last 50 lines
tail -f logfile				#Follow file updates

===================================================================================================================================


EXERCISE 1.5

===================================================================================================================================

ðŸ”¹ 5. Search Files & Directories

find /path -name file		#Find by filename
find . -name "*.log"		#Find by pattern
find . -type f				#Find files only
find . -type d				#Find directories only
find . -empty				#Find empty files/directories
find . -size +10M			#Find files larger than 10MB
find . -mtime -1			#Modified in last 24 hours
locate file					#Fast search (uses database)
updatedb					#Update locate database

===================================================================================================================================

EXERCISE 1.6

===================================================================================================================================

ðŸ”¹ 6. Search Inside Files (Content Search)

grep "text" file			#Search for text
grep -i "text" file			#Case-insensitive search
grep -r "text" .			#Recursively search in all files
grep -n "text" file			#Show line numbers
grep -v "text" file			#Show lines NOT matching
grep -E "pattern"			#Extended regex search
grep -w word file			#Match whole word


===================================================================================================================================

EXERCISE 1.7

===================================================================================================================================

ðŸ”¹ 7. File Size & Disk Usage

du -sh dir					#Directory size summary
du -sh *					#All file/folder sizes
du -m dir					#Size in MB
du -k dir					#Size in KB
du -ah dir					#All files + sizes
df -h						#Disk usage of filesystem
ls -lh file					#File size in human format
stat file					#Detailed size, timestamps
wc -l file					#Count lines
wc -w file					#Count words
wc -c file					#Size in bytes


===================================================================================================================================


EXERCISE 1.8

===================================================================================================================================

ðŸ”¹ 8. Sorting, Filtering, Text Utilities

sort file					#Sort lines alphabetically
sort -n file				#Numeric sort
uniq file					#Remove duplicate lines
uniq -c file				#Count duplicates
cut -d ":" -f1 file			#Cut columns by delimiter
tr a-z A-Z					#Transform text
sed 's/a/b/' file			#Replace text
awk '{print $1}' file		#Print column 1


